# MindBridge Design System
## Purpose
This design system documents the visual and interaction choices used in the 
MindBridge prototype. The goal was to create a calm, trustworthy and accessible 
interface for university students using a mental health and wellness platform.
## Colour Palette
### Primary Colour: Serene Blue `#1F5F97`
Used for main buttons, headings, navigation highlights and key call-to-action 
areas. This colour was selected to communicate trust, calmness and reliability.
### Secondary Colour: Growth Green `#30694C`
Used for wellness-related accents, success messages and supportive visual 
elements. This colour represents wellbeing, growth and emotional progress.
### Background Colour: Off-white `#F9F9FF`
Used as the main page background. It was selected instead of pure white to 
reduce visual strain and create a softer reading experience.
## Typography
### Headline Font: Plus Jakarta Sans
Used for page titles, section headings and important interface labels. It was 
selected because it has a modern, friendly and rounded appearance.
### Body Font: Be Vietnam Pro
Used for paragraphs, form text, descriptions and resource cards. It supports 
readability and clean spacing for longer content.
## Layout and Spacing
The interface uses a clean card-based layout with generous spacing between 
sections. This reduces visual clutter and supports users who may be stressed or overwhelmed

## Buttons and Calls to Action
Primary buttons are used for key actions such as:- Book a Session- Track Your Mood- Login / Register
Rounded corners and clear labels are used to make the interface feel softer and 
easier to use.
## Navigation
The navigation includes five main items:- Home- Resources- Book Appointment- Mood Tracker- Login
The navigation was kept short to reduce cognitive load and make the core 
features easy to access.
## Accessibility Considerations
The interface uses readable font sizes, clear labels and a strong visual 
hierarchy. Important information is communicated through text labels instead of 
relying only on colour.
## Design Rationale Summary
The design system supports the purpose of MindBridge by creating a calm, 
private and student-friendly digital environment. The visual style avoids 
cluttered layouts, aggressive colours and complex interactions.
